Property estimated at more than Sh1.5 million was on Thursday destroyed after the roof of an administration block and four classrooms of Lang&rsquo;u Primary School, Rarieda subcounty, was brought down by strong wind. Double Joy Children&rsquo;s Home was also damaged.The wind followed a heavy down pour that pounded the area for four hours on Wednesday evening.School head teacher Aggrey Abonyo said the school lost property valued at about Sh1.5 million. He said following the incident, more than 130 pupils and the school&rsquo;s staff will learn under trees. ECDE, standard two, three, four and eight classrooms were destroyed. Double Joy Children&rsquo;s Home manager Peter Atin said the roof of a 55-bed dormitory was damaged and more than 50 children are now sleeping in a small room.